*'''HP SDGOB-0991 (1150-7933)''' ''HP Bellatrix'' ([[Foxconn U98Z058]]) This device to be using ''[[Broadcom]]'' BCM94319WLUSBN4L reference design. {{see also|HP|HP SDGOB-0892 (1150-7935)|HP SDGOB-1091 (1150-7944)}}
==Forum threads== *[https://alexkaltsas.wordpress.com/2014/07/22/hacking-a-printerss-wifi-module/#comment-165 ''Hacking a Printer's Wi-Fi Module''] (comments) :A user notes the USB ID of his BCM94319WLUSBN4L pulled from their HP printer as 0a5c:bd16. It's probably the same device. *[https://electronics.stackexchange.com/questions/94244/how-to-connect-a-printer-wifi-module-wires-to-an-arduino/94246 ''How to connect a Printer WIFI module wires to an Arduino?''] :[[Broadcom]] BCM94319WLUSBN4LPT, HP P/N 1150-7933
